The paper deals with property testing, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science that falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem of monotonicity testing is a well-studied problem in discrete mathematics and combinatorics (cs.DM), and the paper specifically deals with monotonicity testing over hypercubes and hypergrids, which are discrete structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and computational geometry (cs.CG) to derive its results. Overall, these sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
